Justification for Mapping: No more specific relation is available.  A table of contents would likely be included in all mainfestations of an  expression.  -- lna 2022-06-28
Transformation Notes: Append to the beginning of the contents of subfield a, the Indicator 2 label followed by colon and space, e.g.   Contents:  Chapter 1.  etc.  .  This could be used to distinguish the note type in discovery systems.  -- lna 2022-06-28

Justification for Mapping: Per RDA, the only recording method applicable to this element is unstructured description .  -- lna 2022-06-29
Transformation Notes: Map separately from subfield a.  Append to the beginning of the contents of subfield u, the indicator 2 label followed by the string (URI) followed by colon and space.  E.g.  Contents (URI):  http://lcweb.loc.gov/catdir/toc/99176484.html   --lna 2022-06-28
Notes (Uncategorized): If there is a subfield a, another choice  might be to append this string at the end of the mapping of subfield a.  This however could be messy (especially if there are multiple subfield u's!) and less likely to be noticed or useful for end users.  A separate mapping could be easier to deal with for interface development if it is desired to present this as a hyperlink.  If there is no subfield a, this separate mapping would work fine too.  --lna 2022-06-29
